  "prompt": "How exactly did they make Monica Geller of Friends look fat in those few episodes?",
  "response": "In the television show \"Friends,\" Monica Geller, played by Courteney Cox, is depicted as having been overweight during her teenage years in several flashback episodes. To achieve this effect, the show's creators used a combination of prosthetics and a fat suit. These specially designed costumes and makeup techniques allowed Courteney Cox to appear significantly heavier than her actual size without affecting her performance ability. The fat suit was padded to create the appearance of weight gain, and makeup was applied to ensure the transformation looked realistic on camera. This approach is a common method in the entertainment industry when a character's physical transformation is essential to the story.",
